-- Reliance Industries, Hinduja Global, HCL Tech, Uflex: India Equity Preview
-- Vipin V. Nair
-- 2010-06-22T02:55:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/reliance-industries-hinduja-global-hcl-tech-uflex-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange’s Sensitive Index, or  Sensex ,
gained 305.73, or 1.7 percent, to 17,876.55. The S&P CNX  Nifty 
Index on the National Stock Exchange rose 1.7 percent to
5,353.30. The BSE 200 Index increased 1.7 percent to 2,252.69.
SGX CNX Nifty Index futures for June delivery lost 0.3 to
5,337.5 at 10:40 a.m. in Singapore.  
 HCL Technologies Ltd.  (HCLT IN): The software services
company may merge its business with  HCL Infosystems Ltd.  (HCLI
IN), CNBC-TV18 television channel reported, without saying where
it got the information.  Vineet Nayar , chief executive officer of
HCL Technologies, and  Ajai Chowdhry , chairman and chief
executive officer of HCL Infosystems, weren’t available to
comment after normal office hours in New Delhi. HCL Technologies
fell 0.3 percent to 388.25 rupees. HCL Infosystems gained 0.7
percent to 120.2 rupees.  
 Hinduja Global Solutions Ltd.  (HGSL IN): The technology
services provider agreed to buy Careline Services, a U.K.-based
customer relationship management company, it said in a statement
to the Bombay Stock Exchange. Hinduja Global rose 0.1 percent to
441.1 rupees.  
 Ranbaxy Laboratories Ltd.  (RBXY IN)) The company has no
plan to close the Mohali bulk-drug manufacturing plant in India,
a spokesman for the company’s majority owner said. The plant
will continue operating,  Satoru Ogawa , a spokesman for Tokyo-
based Daiichi Sankyo Co., said by telephone today. Ranbaxy
gained 1.5 percent to 446.95 rupees.  
 Reliance Industries Ltd.  (RIL IN): The operator of India’s
biggest gas area and the world’s largest refining complex may
supply natural gas for  Anil Ambani ’s power companies within a
year, Bloomberg UTV reported, citing people it didn’t identify.
Reliance Industries spokesman  Manoj Warrier  declined to comment.
Ravi Sodhi, a spokesman for the Anil Dhirubhai Ambani Group,
didn’t pick up calls to his mobile phone seeking comment.
Reliance Industries rose 1.1 percent to 1,065.65 rupees.  
 SpiceJet Ltd.  (SJET IN): India is investigating an
allegation that SpiceJet carried more passengers than its
capacity on a New Delhi-Mumbai flight earlier this month, the
Mint newspaper reported, citing a spokeswoman it didn’t identify
from the Ministry of Civil Aviation. SpiceJet’s Chief Executive
Officer  Sanjay Aggarwal  wasn’t immediately available to comment
when called at his office. The stock gained 0.8 percent to 60.35
rupees.  
 Suven Life Sciences Ltd.  (SVLS IN): The company is scouting
for a global partner to sell new drugs after winning discovery
patents for treatments of some most common ailments, the Mint
newspaper reported, citing Chief Executive  Venkateswarlu Jasti .
Suven fell 0.3 percent to 29.7 rupees.  
 Uflex Ltd.  (UFLX IN): The maker of plastic packaging
materials plans to raise as much as 2.5 billion rupees through a
rights offer of shares, the company said in a statement to the
Bombay Stock Exchange. The shares rose 1.8 percent to 114.4
rupees.  
